name: Arithmetic
excerpt: the branch of mathematics dealing with the properties and manipulation of numbers.

name: Trigonometry
excerpt: the branch of mathematics dealing with the relations of the sides and angles of triangles and with the relevant functions of any angles.

name: Statistics
excerpt: Statistics is a branch of mathematics dealing with the collection, analysis, interpretation, presentation, and organization of data.

name: Geometry
excerpt: the branch of mathematics concerned with the properties and relations of points, lines, surfaces, solids, and higher dimensional analogues.

name: Probability
excerpt: Probability is the measure of the likelihood that an event will occur. Probability is quantified as a number between 0 and 1,

name: Co-ordinate
excerpt: In classical mathematics, analytic geometry, also known as coordinate geometry, or in a common manifestation Cartesian geometry, is the study of geometry using a coordinate system.

name: Vectors
excerpt: In mathematics, a Euclidean vector (sometimes called a geometric or spatial vector, or—as here—simply a vector) is a geometric object that has magnitude (or length) and direction. Vectors can be added to other vectors according to vector algebra.

name: 3D
excerpt: Three-dimensional space (also: 3-space or, rarely, tri-dimensional space) is a geometric setting in which three values (called parameters) are required to determine the position of an element
